<grammar>
yue:「從頭再嚟」係一個動詞短語，可以帶賓語。
eng:"從頭再嚟" is a verb phrase that can take an object. 

yue:例如：「我哋可以從頭再嚟呢個計劃。」
eng:For example: "We can start over this plan." 

yue:呢個短語可以用喺句首、句中或者句尾。
eng:This phrase can be used at the beginning, middle, or end of a sentence. 

<collocation>
yue:從頭再嚟 + 計劃/工作/項目
eng:to start over + plan/work/project 

yue:從頭再嚟 + 生活/學習/感情
eng:to start over + life/study/relationship 

<example>
yue:雖然今次考試唔合格，但係我可以從頭再嚟。（seon1 mat6 gam1 ci3 hou2 sik1 m4 kap1 gaak3, daan6 hai6 ngo5 ho2 ji5 cung4 tau4 zoi3 lei4.）
eng:Although I failed this exam, I can start over. 

yue:呢個生意失敗咗，但係我哋可以從頭再嚟。（ni1 go3 sang1 ji3 sat1 baai6 zo2, daan6 hai6 ngo5 dei6 ho2 ji5 cung4 tau4 zoi3 lei4.）
eng:This business failed, but we can start over. 

<note>
yue:「從頭再嚟」同「重新開始」有啲似，但「從頭再嚟」強調由最初嘅階段重新開始，而「重新開始」可以係任何階段。
eng:"從頭再嚟" is similar to "重新開始", but "從頭再嚟" emphasizes starting over from the initial stage, while "重新開始" can be at any stage. 

yue:例如：「我哋可以從頭再嚟呢個計劃。」同「我哋可以重新開始呢個計劃。」意思有少少唔同。
eng:For example: "We can start over this plan." and "We can restart this plan." have slightly different meanings. 

<usage>
yue:「從頭再嚟」可以用喺正面或者負面嘅情況。
eng:"從頭再嚟" can be used in both positive and negative situations. 

yue:正面：「雖然失敗，但我哋可以從頭再嚟。」
eng:Positive: "Although we failed, we can start over." 

yue:負面：「呢個計劃搞到一鑊粥，要從頭再嚟。」
eng:Negative: "This plan has turned into a mess, we need to start over." 

